&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are PMG&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Named Ad Age Best Places to Work for 11 years in a row and Fast Company Best Workplaces for Innovators since 2022, PMG is a global independent marketing services and technology company that seeks to inspire people and brands that anything is possible. Driven by shared success, PMG utilises business strategy and transformation, creative, media, and insights—as well as its proprietary operating system, Alli—to deliver cutting-edge digital solutions and innovative media strategies. Our team comprises 1,000 employees globally, and our work for ambitious brands like Apple, Peloton, Nike, Creed Fragrances, Experian, BNY, Sephora, Therabody, and Travelex spans 85+ countries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Who You Will Be Working With&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a Creative Copywriting Senior Associate, you’ll be part of a creative team that cares deeply about craft—writers, designers, producers, and creative leads who like pushing ideas further while keeping the work grounded in what the audience actually feels and needs. You’ll partner closely with creative leadership to shape concepts, refine language, and bring strong copy to life across different formats and channels.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You’ll also collaborate with strategy and account teammates who help clarify the “why” behind the work—audience insight, brand goals, and the role each message plays in a bigger campaign. At times, you’ll work directly with clients, presenting copy directions, explaining your thinking, and helping teams land on language that feels true to the brand and clear to the customer.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You Will Be Doing&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write original, engaging copy across a range of projects—campaigns, brand storytelling, product and service messaging, and content systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt your voice quickly and thoughtfully, capturing the tone and personality of multiple brands without losing clarity or consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take briefs from early concept to polished execution, exploring different angles and elevating ideas through strong language and structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present copy and creative concepts with confidence, explaining how the work supports both the creative vision and the business goal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring sharp attention to detail—tight edits, clean grammar, and wording that feels intentional in every headline, CTA, and long-form line.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spot content opportunities by paying attention to audience behavior, customer needs, and cultural moments that can make messaging feel more relevant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on trends in advertising, design, and culture, using what you learn to strengthen the work (not distract from it).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use available tools—including AI where helpful—to speed up exploration, sharpen drafts, and streamline workflows while keeping the final voice human and brand-true.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
